Executive Summary
This activity documents the use of multiple AI agents to support the design and development of a personal investment tracking system intended to calculate Romanian investment taxes and assist with fiscal reporting obligations.
During the development process, the user conducted a practical evaluation of AI agent capabilities, reliability patterns, and hallucination risks when tasked with generating complex deliverables involving financial calculations and legal considerations.
The results of this evaluation led to the development of a revised AI interaction methodology based on modular prompting, staged development, and systematic validation. The activity therefore served both as a technical project (investment tracker development) and as a structured case study on effective AI usage in complex analytical workflows.

Project Objective
The primary objective was to design a Romanian Investment Tax Master File, implemented as an Excel-based investment tracker capable of:
	• calculating Romanian investment taxes correctly
	• supporting multiple categories of investment income
	• maintaining traceable calculations suitable for verification
	• supporting long-term portfolio tracking across multiple years
	• remaining modular and expandable as fiscal legislation evolves
The system must also support manual verification of all calculations in order to ensure fiscal accuracy and audit readiness.

AI-Assisted Development Context
The development process relied on AI agents as analytical and documentation assistants. The user experimented with several agents in their free versions, including ChatGPT and Copilot, using them for:
	• structuring project documentation
	• organizing technical requirements
	• refining design specifications
	• assisting with spreadsheet architecture planning
This process was also intended as a practical exercise in AI literacy, prompt engineering, and workflow optimization.

Initial Development Approach
The initial strategy involved asking AI agents to generate a complete investment tracking system in a single workflow.
The requested deliverable included:
	• multi-category investment tracking
	• Romanian fiscal logic
	• FIFO lot tracking
	• foreign exchange conversion logic
	• tax calculations across multiple income types
	• CASS threshold calculations
	• structured reporting for ANAF declarations
While the agents were able to generate partially functional files, repeated attempts revealed reliability issues.

Observed AI Behavior and Limitations
During testing, several consistent patterns were observed.
Both ChatGPT and Copilot demonstrated strong capabilities when producing long explanations or structured informational content. Examples of successful outputs included:
	• language learning support
	• health and supplement explanations
	• learning plans for new skills
	• general informational legal explanations
However, reliability decreased significantly when the user requested highly complex outputs that required simultaneous execution of multiple tasks.
The agents occasionally produced outputs that contained:
	• missing calculation logic
	• incomplete financial structures
	• omitted legal considerations
	• partially implemented features
	• structural inconsistencies
For example, several generated investment tracking files omitted critical elements such as:
	• FIFO per lot tracking logic
	• certain tax calculation conditions
	• specific fiscal requirements
In some cases, the generation process stopped prematurely or produced incomplete deliverables.

Strategic Methodology Revision
Based on these observations, the initial development strategy was abandoned and replaced with a modular AI interaction framework.
The revised methodology focuses on reducing complexity per interaction and validating results incrementally.
Key principles include:
	• clearly defining the overall objective before development begins
	• breaking complex tasks into small, manageable modules
	• implementing one feature at a time
	• validating each module before continuing development
	• maintaining intermediate file versions for backup and comparison
This modular approach significantly reduces hallucination risk and improves the reliability of AI-assisted outputs.

Dual Development Strategy
Two parallel approaches were defined for continuing the project.
Approach 1 – Existing Chat Recovery
The existing conversation containing the previous investment tracker attempts will be analyzed in order to determine whether the partially generated files can be salvaged and improved.
This includes reviewing previous prompts and extracting useful elements that may still be valid.
Approach 2 – Clean Development Environment
A new AI conversation will be initiated with a fully redesigned prompting strategy.
The new workflow will focus on:
	• small incremental requests
	• isolated module development
	• strict validation before feature expansion
	• continuous documentation of results
Both approaches will be evaluated in order to determine the most reliable workflow.

Investment Tracker Specification
A comprehensive specification was developed defining the architecture of the Romanian Investment Tax Master File.
The specification includes the following functional modules:
	• settings configuration module
	• foreign exchange management system
	• stock transaction tracking
	• dividend income tracking
	• FIFO lot tracking engine
	• Forex trading result reporting
	• cryptocurrency transaction tracking
	• royalties and miscellaneous income reporting
	• loss carryforward engine with seven-year tracking
	• tax calculation engine per income category
	• CASS calculation module based on Romanian thresholds
	• ANAF declaration summary output
	• optional financial dashboard
	• full documentation module explaining usage and logic
The architecture is designed to maintain full transparency and traceability of calculations.

Design Principles
The system must follow several strict design principles.
These include:
	• transparent formulas with no hidden logic
	• no circular references
	• no unstable or volatile formulas
	• no hidden macros unless explicitly approved
	• clear modular spreadsheet structure
	• manual override capability for complex inputs such as foreign exchange rates
The file must also support future expansion and legislative updates.

AI Usage Methodology
The project also serves as a structured exercise in AI workflow optimization.
The user deliberately experiments with multiple AI systems to better understand their capabilities and limitations.
The operational AI interaction workflow now follows these steps:
	1. Define the objective clearly.
	2. Break the project into small functional modules.
	3. Generate and validate one module at a time.
	4. Save intermediate results.
	5. Continue development only after verification.
This methodology allows AI to be used as a controlled development assistant rather than an autonomous system builder.

Future Activities
The next stages of the project include:
	• creating the new AI development chat
	• implementing the specification module by module
	• validating the generated Excel file at each stage
	• testing the system with sample investment data
	• documenting the entire process as a portfolio case study
The project will continue to serve as both a financial data management tool and a practical AI workflow experiment.

Outcome
This activity resulted in:
	• the design of a comprehensive investment tracker specification
	• the identification of AI reliability limitations during complex tasks
	• the development of a structured modular prompting methodology
	• improved understanding of AI-assisted workflow design
The resulting methodology significantly improves the reliability and usefulness of AI tools when applied to complex analytical projects.

